            <title>[CAMEL-8950] Injected Quartz2 scheduler doesn&apos;t have access to CamelContext in jobs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8950</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently if you inject a scheduler the CamelContext won&apos;t be available for jobs to access. When the scheduler is created automatically, the context is added to the quartz scheduler context so the jobs can access it:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;quartzContext.put(QuartzConstants.QUARTZ_CAMEL_CONTEXT + &quot;-&quot; + camelContextName, getCamelContext());&lt;/p&gt;</description>
